:::summary
Rivers are the arteries of the earth — flowing channels of fresh water that have nourished every great civilization in human history, carved the landscapes we inhabit, and served as powerful symbols of life, purification, and divine provision throughout Scripture. From the four rivers of Eden to the Jordan, the Nile, the Tigris and Euphrates, and the great rivers of the American continent, these moving waters have been inseparable from the story of humanity's relationship with God, the land, and each other.
